    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_Timeout">Request timed out. Ensure the WSL service is running or increase the HTTP timeout in Settings.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_HttpConnection">Could not reach the WSL service. Check that the Go binary is running in WSL and the address in Settings. On WSL2, if the service is running but 127.0.0.1 still fails, use Fill WSL IP in Settings or set the base URL to http://IP:17890/ with the IP from wsl hostname -I on Windows (localhost does not always forward).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_Unauthorized">Access denied (401). Check that the API token in Settings matches DOCKLITE_API_TOKEN on the WSL service, then Save.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_Forbidden">Access forbidden (403). Check permissions or reverse-proxy / token configuration.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_NotFound">Resource not found (404). Check the API path or whether the container/image ID was removed.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_RequestTimeoutHttp">Server-side timeout (408). The service or Docker may be overloaded; retry or increase the HTTP timeout in Settings.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_TooManyRequests">Too many requests (429). Wait a few seconds and try again.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_ServerError">Internal server error (500). Check the Go service logs in WSL or the application log.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_BadGateway">Bad gateway (502). The reverse proxy or Docker Engine may be unavailable; check WSL and Docker.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Error_Network_ServiceUnavailable">Service unavailable (503). Docker Engine may not be running or the service is still starting.</sys:String>

