    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Dashboard_Title">Dashboard</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Dashboard_Body" xml:space="preserve">The Dashboard shows WSL service status (health) and Docker Engine information from the API.

Refresh: reloads data from the service. The Go service in WSL must be running and DockLite must use the correct address in Settings.

If there is no response: check Settings (base URL, auto-start WSL), or run wsl-docker-service manually in WSL.

Press F5 to refresh the current page (except Settings and Cleanup).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Containers_Title">Containers</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Containers_Body" xml:space="preserve">Docker container list. Filter by state; search by name, image, ID.

Select: pick multiple rows for bulk actions. Select all / Clear selection control the checkboxes.

Start selected / Stop selected / Delete selected / Copy selected IDs: only applies to checked rows; Start only when a container is stopped, Stop when it is running.

Highlighted row: Start, Stop, Restart, Delete, Load details (inspect + stats). The expanded section can enable realtime stats: REST polling on an interval or a WebSocket stream (fewer requests). You can choose a higher WebSocket interval (ms) when many containers are open or the network is slow to reduce load.

CPU and RAM % sparklines: update when realtime is on (or one point after Load details); the horizontal axis is time (newest on the right), up to 90 points.

Top RAM / Top CPU: snapshots from the server (not a full ranked list).

Press F5 to refresh the container list while you are on the Containers page.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Logs_Title">Container logs</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Logs_Body" xml:space="preserve">View container stdout/stderr. Pick a container, tail line count, optional search.

Search: for very long lines, matching uses only the leading part (see tooltip). Line colouring by log level keywords also looks at the start of the line to avoid heavy work.

Load containers: refresh the list to choose from. Load tail: fetch the log tail once.

Follow (WS): streamed logs; how often lines appear on screen backs off when the buffer is large or processing a batch is slow. Clear view: clears the on-screen text only.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Compose_Title">Docker Compose</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Compose_Body" xml:space="preserve">Manage Docker Compose project folders and run compose commands through the service in WSL.

Add a project folder (Windows or WSL path), select a project in the grid, pick a service from the compose file.

Multiple compose files: one relative path per line inside the project folder (like multiple -f on the CLI); the service accepts up to 16 files; you can edit after adding with Save compose files.

You can start/stop services, view service logs, run exec without a TTY. Compose command output appears in the panel below.

Open WSL terminal in project folder: runs wsl.exe (distro from Settings if set) to open bash in the project folder — for compose exec -it or interactive shells outside DockLite.

Refresh list: sync saved projects; compose up/down/ps: runs in WSL in the project folder.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Images_Title">Images</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Images_Body" xml:space="preserve">Docker image list. Search by repository, tag, ID. Use Select to choose multiple images.

Expanded block: inspect JSON, layer history, pull by reference (log may be truncated), export tar (docker save) and import tar (docker load). Pull, export and import run on a background thread so the UI stays responsive; the call may still take a long time until the server finishes.

Delete selected rows / Delete image (highlighted row): remove images. Copy selected IDs: copies full IDs for checked rows. Prune dangling / prune unused: calls prune via the API (data loss risk).

Select all / Clear selection: similar to containers; use the buttons only when the right rows are selected.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_NetworkVolume_Title">Networks and volumes</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_NetworkVolume_Body" xml:space="preserve">Lists networks and volumes from Docker Engine (GET /api/networks and /api/volumes). Refresh reloads both grids.

View only; create or delete networks or volumes with the Docker CLI or Compose.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Cleanup_Title">Cleanup</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Cleanup_Body" xml:space="preserve">Runs docker prune commands in WSL (container, image, volume, network, system prune). Each command can delete data permanently.

Read the warnings in the README. System prune including volumes is especially dangerous.

Output shows results from the service. Run only when you understand the impact.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_AppDebugLog_Title">Application log</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_AppDebugLog_Body" xml:space="preserve">Reads DockLite’s own log files on Windows by day, with filters for category, level, and text.

On-screen time columns use the time zone and format from Settings — Display (after Save).

Refresh: reload; Open log folder: Explorer; Copy diagnostics / Export log: helps when reporting issues.

The log folder path is read-only in the UI.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Settings_Title">Settings</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Settings_Body" xml:space="preserve">Settings has tabs: Connection (base URL, optional API token matching DOCKLITE_API_TOKEN on WSL, HTTP timeout), WSL &amp; service (auto-start, service folder, distro, Windows source and Unix destination when syncing Go code, optional VERSION enforcement, uname/wslpath tests), Display (time zone, date/time format, preview), Wait &amp; health (wait after spawning WSL, manual Start/Restart wait, per-poll timeout, poll interval).

Save writes everything to the settings file. Bottom row: Build service (go build in WSL), Start / Stop / Restart, Test connection.

Fill in the WSL IP when localhost does not forward to WSL2. Health wait times are no longer fixed: adjust them on Wait &amp; health, then Save.

If connection or WSL fails: see the repo README (build service, environment variables, GET /api/openapi.json); LAN security and proxy: docs/docklite-lan-security.md; API tokens: docs/docklite-api-token.md.

On Settings, F5 does not run a network check — use «Test connection» or Save (Save may trigger a background /api/health check).</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_DockLite_Title">DockLite</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_NoPage_Body">No page is selected.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Ui_Help_Unknown_Body">There is no help text for this screen.</sys:String>
